&lt;h3&gt;System tests&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;system-tests&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#system-tests&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;For full end-to-end testing with a browser, Rails system tests work exactly as normal — Phlex views are just HTML from the browser&amp;rsquo;s perspective:&lt;/p&gt;
